LORE mafdet-priest
FLAGS MAFDET PRIEST
- Shrine of the First Claw: civic-judicial facility, not a conventional temple;
  the guardian Mafdet enforces trust, does not bless commerce
- Oath Chamber: trade oaths sealed on the basalt First Claw sculpture (worn
  smooth by centuries of use); recorded on wax-and-bitumen tablet; the witness
  is simultaneously spiritual and legally binding
- Guardian Mafdet predates the corridor's dynastic religions; independent of
  Solar Court, Moon Sovereign, and Jackal Synod authority
- Jackal Synod claims universal funerary/oath jurisdiction across the eastern
  corridor; the Shrine's position: Synod jurisdiction ends where the sea begins
- Salt-oath formulas (Eastern Desert tradition) are tolerated as personal
  religious choice; not legally binding in Mafdet's commercial courts
- Strand Rememberers maintain guardian origin stories and navigational knowledge
  predating the corridor civilization; the pre-institutional history of the
  Shrine
~
